{% set basicRtCode %}<ruby>
  漢字 <rt>かんじ</rt>
</ruby>{% endset %}

{% set withRpCode %}<ruby>
  東京 <rp>(</rp><rt>とうきょう</rt><rp>)</rp>
</ruby>{% endset %}

{% set individualRtCode %}<ruby>
  漢 <rt>かん</rt>
  字 <rt>じ</rt>
</ruby>{% endset %}

{% set pinyinRtCode %}<ruby>
  中文 <rt>zhōngwén</rt>
</ruby>{% endset %}

{% set rtCssCode %}rt {
  font-size: 0.5em;
  line-height: 1;
  ruby-align: center;
}

/* CJK script font for ruby text */
:lang(ja) rt, :lang(zh) rt, :lang(ko) rt {
  font-family: var(--font-cjk);
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> element specifies the ruby text &mdash; the small annotation that appears above (or beside) base text. It must be contained within a <a href="/docs/elements/native/ruby/"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a> element.</p>
    <p>VB styles <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> at <code>0.5em</code> font size with centered alignment, and applies CJK script fonts when inside a CJK language context. The <a href="/docs/i18n/">i18n system</a> can control <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> visibility via <code>data-ruby</code> on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Inside <a href="/docs/elements/native/ruby/"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a> to provide pronunciation guides</li>
      <li>Japanese furigana (hiragana readings for kanji)</li>
      <li>Chinese pinyin (romanized pronunciation)</li>
      <li>Pronunciation guides for words in any language</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/ruby-annotations.html" url="ruby-annotations.html" title="Ruby text examples" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic rt">{{ basicRtCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="With fallback parentheses">{{ withRpCode | escape }}</code-block>
