  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="rt CSS">{{ rtCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Visibility Control</h2>
    <p>The <a href="/docs/i18n/">i18n system</a> provides <code>data-ruby</code> on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> to control when <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> annotations display: <code>show</code> (always), <code>hide</code> (visually hidden but accessible), or <code>auto</code> (CJK languages only). See the <a href="/docs/elements/native/ruby/">ruby element page</a> for details.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers may read base text followed by ruby text, or offer options to hear annotations</li>
      <li>Ruby text is valuable for language learners and those with reading difficulties</li>
      <li>When <code>data-ruby="hide"</code> is used, <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> is visually hidden but remains in the DOM for screen readers</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

